title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson Model 66 Stainless 4-inch Barrel
postcontent:
Smith and Wesson Model 66 Stainless Steel. ALL ORIGINAL. THE ACTION ON THIS GUN IS "BUTTER SMOOTH". Single action pull is about 1.5 lbs. This gun is VERY NICE.

Model 66 is a double-action six-shot revolver that can also be fired single action. This revolver will accept and safely shoot both 357 Magnum and 38 Special ammo, including extra-hot 38 ammunition known as "plus-p" (+P) and "plus-p-plus" (+P+). 

Gun has a red ramp front sight (sight is built integral with barrel and has a red plastic insert), ramp up frame and barrel, and adjustable rear sight. Pinned barrel and recessed cylinders (no longer made like this, as the process is too expensive). 

I have honestly never fired it. The gentleman who bought it new fired it less than 50 times (according to his widow). I bought it from her. 

This particular revolver has the "target trigger". The hammer is the S&W target hammer with a spur that's 1/2" wide. The wood grips (called "stocks" by Smith & Wesson) are original made of goncalo alves wood, and are of the "target" type with the original S&W medallion imbedded on both sides. THE WOOD IS BEAUTIFUL ON THIS GUN.

THIS IS A COLLECTOR GRADE GUN. These guns are getting hard to find, as collectors are not selling them. This gun has not been fired very much, very little cylinder ring marking. 

Here is your chance to have the best of both worlds; a COLLECTOR GRADE GUN THAT ALSO CAN BE USED AS A SHOOTER. 

Additional photos available upon request.

The MP-25 can hold six .25 ACP rounds in the magazine, plus one in the chamber, and is finished in chrome. The grips are imitation mother-of-pearl handles. 

Early models have a sliding bar safety that will not allow the pistol to chamber a round or cock the striker if the safety is not in the fire position when the slide is pulled back. Later models have a push up safety that will not allow the action to be cycled at all when engaged.
